<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2 id="section---PhysicalHealthExamples">Physical Health Examples</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The interconnectedness of physical health with the other dimensions of well-being emphasizes its importance. Being a physically healthy person can involve a variety of activities.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li><strong>Aerobic Activities:&nbsp;</strong>Activities involving moving the large muscles of the body. Walking, running, swimming, and biking are all examples of aerobic activities. Aerobic exercise improves the function of the cardiovascular system, and it can lower the risk of several chronic diseases such as heart disease and type 2 diabetes.</li><li><strong>Muscle-strengthening Activities:</strong>&nbsp;Activities often involving resistance or weights. They require the body to work against applied force or weight. Pushups, situps, squats, and weight training are all examples of muscle-strengthening activities. These activities help to maintain or increase strength and muscle mass.</li><li><strong>Bone-strengthening Activities:</strong>&nbsp;Activities applying a force to the bones, often by causing an impact with the ground. Running, walking, and jumping rope are examples of bone-strengthening activities. These activities increase bone strength.</li><li><strong>Stretching Activities</strong>: Activities promoting flexibility and increased movement. Yoga and stretching exercises fall into this category.</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2 id="section---PhysicalHealthCharacteristics">Physical Health Characteristics</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>A physically healthy person has several key characteristics in his or her life.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li><strong>Healthy lifestyle</strong>: This person's lifestyle is one that promotes activity and wellness. Rather than being sedentary, a physically healthy person will incorporate daily activity into their life.</li><li><strong>Healthy diet</strong>: A physically healthy person will eat a healthy diet. This type of diet includes many fruits and vegetables, lean proteins, and whole grains. It is a diet low in sugar and saturated fats.</li><li><strong>Consistent exercise</strong>: Good physical health requires regular exercise. A physically healthy person will incorporate a variety of regular exercise activities into their routine.</li><li><strong>Regular health screenings</strong>: A physically healthy person will take preventative measures including regular wellness exams and health screenings.</li><li><strong>Good Sleep</strong>: Sleep is an important part of the life of a healthy person. Routines and adequate nightly sleep lead to better physical health.</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->
